External knowledge used:
- The term "latest" implies ordering by date/time in descending order (newest first); 
- Access logs are records of when and how pins were accessed by users; 
- Pin versions and test results are important for understanding the current state and functionality of the pins.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(document_id) AS document_count
FROM pin_documents
WHERE pin_id = 1;

SELECT MAX(version_number) AS latest_version
FROM pin_versions
WHERE pin_id = 1;

SELECT pin_name 
FROM pins 
ORDER BY pin_name;
